**No-Load Test**   
Noise testing of the DC-DC converter is conducted with no load connected to the device's output. The test environment includes an oscilloscope set to 20 Hz in AC coupling mode. The power outlet supplies current to all devices in the room, including lights, the oscilloscope, and the power supply. The expected Noise outcome at No Load connected is below 50mV RMS

1. **32V Input / 0V Output**

At 0V the Input (yellow waveform) noise of 5.02mV, is filtered to 1.68mV at Output (blue waveform). This shows that the filtering capacity of the DC-DC Converter is exceptional.
